article.description: Duquesne pulls away late to beat Wagner 34-7
article.headline: Duquesne pulls away late to beat Wagner 34-7
article.linkText: Duquesne pulls away late to beat Wagner 34-7
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- Ryan Ho, Devin Rahming and Ethan Dorsey each scored touchdowns in the fourth quarter to help Duquesne pull ahead for a 34-7 Northeast Conference win over Wagner Saturday. Leading 10-7 going into the final quarter, the Dukes (3-2, 1-0 NEC) scored on four of their last five drives, starting with a 2-yard touchdown run by Ho. After an Austin Crimmins field goal and a forced three-and-out by the Duquesne defense, Rahming returned a punt 62 yards for a score. Dorsey rushed 40 yards for a touchdown late in the game to fuel the rout. Dillon Buechel went 25-of-37 for 189 yards with a touchdown and two interceptions. His 12-yard strike to Chris King came in the first quarter. Dominique Williams led the Seahawks (2-5, 1-2) with 92 yards rushing. Matthias McKinnon ran for 57 yards and Wagner's only score, a 15-yard run in the second quarter to pull within 3.
